ENCRYPTING SECRET DATA at REST:
Data stored in secrets is not encrypted, you can view yaml file of secrets and decode it.

So, we need to check how the Data stored in the ETCD for the secrets.

Basically we need to run below command with the secrets name we created to check the data encryption
# ETCDCTL_API=3 etcdctl \
   --cacert=/etc/kubernetes/pki/etcd/ca.crt   \
   --cert=/etc/kubernetes/pki/etcd/server.crt \
   --key=/etc/kubernetes/pki/etcd/server.key  \
   get /registry/secrets/default/secret1 | hexdump -C


# etcdctl is working or not to check
# apt-get install etcd-client
# etcdctl works

Check ETCD pods available
# kubectl get pods -n kube-system
# kubectl describe pods etcs-controlplane -n kube-system
# ls /etc/kubernetes/pki/etcd/ (it will list all ca.cert ca.key....)
# created secret is myapp-secret

Now run
ETCDCTL_API=3 etcdctl \
   --cacert=/etc/kubernetes/pki/etcd/ca.crt   \
   --cert=/etc/kubernetes/pki/etcd/server.crt \
   --key=/etc/kubernetes/pki/etcd/server.key  \
   get /registry/secrets/default/myapp-secret | hexdump -C

encrypted secrets data is visible while running this command.


We need to check the encryption at rest is enabled in ETCD or not?
Check --encryption-provider-config is avaiable in kube-apiserver, if not enable it

# ps -aux | grep kube-api | grep "--encryption-provider-config"
# ls /etc/kubernetes/manifest/kube-apiserver.yaml


# head -c 32 /dev/urandom | base64 (use to encode the value)
C1ePo9SK7XOEN0y2cUldPCuuQ/PCWRsqkyh/z4PdFvY=

To enable --encryption-provider-config in the kube-apiserver, we need to create a definition file for encryption-provider-config 
enc.yaml
apiVersion: apiserver.config.k8s.io/v1
kind: EncryptionConfiguration
resources:
  - resources:
      - secrets
      - configmaps
      - pandas.awesome.bears.example
    providers:
      - aescbc:
          keys:
            - name: key1
              secret: <BASE 64 ENCODED SECRET> C1ePo9SK7XOEN0y2cUldPCuuQ/PCWRsqkyh/z4PdFvY=
      - identity: {}

# cat enc.yaml

# mkdir /etc/kubernetes/enc
# mv enc.yaml (enc.yaml from root to /etc/kubernetes/env)

